- It's nonsense anyway.

913
01:07:27,360 --> 01:07:30,520
Why put us through this mumbo jumbo?
Bring on the main course.

914
01:07:30,600 --> 01:07:33,200
I apologise for my disrespectful sister.

915
01:07:33,280 --> 01:07:36,600
This is the twentieth century.
You have young boys sitting here.

916
01:07:36,680 --> 01:07:41,040
- Don't fill their heads with superstition.
- The intellectual. The schoolteacher.

917
01:07:41,120 --> 01:07:43,760
Spare us your Leninist philosophy
just this once.

918
01:07:43,840 --> 01:07:46,560
Afraid if you don't obey the rules
God'll punish you?

919
01:07:46,640 --> 01:07:49,840
- Not me, May. He punishes the wicked.
- Who? Like Hitler?

920
01:07:49,920 --> 01:07:52,720
- We're having a Seder!
- Six million Jews burned to death

921
01:07:52,800 --> 01:07:55,720
- and they got away with it.
- How did they get away with it?

922
01:07:55,800 --> 01:07:59,320
Come on, Sol, open your eyes!
Six million Jews and millions of others.

923
01:07:59,440 --> 01:08:02,000
- And they got off.
- How could humans do such a thing?

924
01:08:02,080 --> 01:08:04,080
Because might makes right.

925
01:08:04,160 --> 01:08:07,480
- Until the Americans marched in...
- I don't like this talk at my Seder.

926
01:08:07,560 --> 01:08:09,680
OK, OK! All right!

927
01:08:09,760 --> 01:08:11,760
I think this is interesting.

928
01:08:13,400 --> 01:08:17,560
You know, there's this joke about
the prizefighter who enters the ring.

929
01:08:17,640 --> 01:08:21,040
And his brother says to the family priest
"Father, pray for him."

930
01:08:21,120 --> 01:08:23,960
The priest said "I will.
But if he can punch, it'll help."

931
01:08:24,040 --> 01:08:28,440
What are you saying, May? You challenge
the whole moral structure of everything?

932
01:08:28,520 --> 01:08:32,560
What moral structure? Is that the kind
of nonsense you use on your pupils?

933
01:08:32,640 --> 01:08:36,000
Do you not find human impulses
basically decent?

934
01:08:36,120 --> 01:08:39,800
- There's basically nothing.
- Such a cynic, my sister. A nihilist.

935
01:08:39,920 --> 01:08:42,160
- Back to Russia!
- Well... Listen.

936
01:08:42,240 --> 01:08:46,120
I happen to agree with May
when it comes to all that mumbo jumbo.

937
01:08:46,200 --> 01:08:50,280
How can you say that? You come
to every Seder. You pray in Hebrew.

938
01:08:50,360 --> 01:08:54,240
Yes. I'm going through the motions.
It's like any ritual. It's a habit.

939
01:08:54,320 --> 01:08:58,160
What are you saying, May? There's
no morality anywhere in the whole world?

940
01:08:58,240 --> 01:09:00,960
For those who want morality,
there's morality.

941
01:09:01,040 --> 01:09:04,880
- Nothing's handed down in stone.
- Sol's kind of faith is a gift.

942
01:09:04,960 --> 01:09:07,960
It's like an ear for music,
or the talent to draw.

943
01:09:08,040 --> 01:09:11,320
He believes. You can use logic
on him and he still believes.

944
01:09:11,400 --> 01:09:13,200
Must everything be logical?

945
01:09:13,280 --> 01:09:15,840
And if a man commits a crime,

946
01:09:15,920 --> 01:09:19,120
if he... if he kills...

947
01:09:20,160 --> 01:09:23,760
- One way or another he will be punished.
- If he's caught, Sol.

948
01:09:23,840 --> 01:09:28,440
If he's not, that which originates from a
black deed will blossom in a foul manner.

949
01:09:28,560 --> 01:09:31,560
- You're relying too heavily on the Bible.
- No, no, no.

950
01:09:31,640 --> 01:09:35,680
Whether it's the Old Testament
or Shakespeare, murder will out.

951
01:09:36,280 --> 01:09:39,640
- Who said anything about murder?
- You did.

952
01:09:41,920 --> 01:09:43,920
Did I?

953
01:09:45,320 --> 01:09:47,840
And I say,
if he can do it and get away with it

954
01:09:47,920 --> 01:09:50,640
and he chooses
not to be bothered by the ethics,

955
01:09:50,720 --> 01:09:52,120
then he's home free.

956
01:09:52,200 --> 01:09:55,160
Remember,
history is written by the winners.

957
01:09:55,240 --> 01:10:00,520
If the Nazis had won, future generations
would see World War II quite differently.

958
01:10:00,600 --> 01:10:04,760
Your aunt is a brilliant woman, Judah,
but she's had a very unhappy life.

959
01:10:04,840 --> 01:10:07,440
And if all your faith is wrong, Sol?

960
01:10:07,520 --> 01:10:10,040
Just what if, huh? If?

961
01:10:10,120 --> 01:10:13,120
I'll still have a better life
than all of those that doubt.

962
01:10:13,200 --> 01:10:17,240
Wait a minute. Are you telling me
that you prefer God to the truth?

963
01:10:17,320 --> 01:10:20,160
If necessary,
I will always choose God over truth.

964
01:10:20,240 --> 01:10:22,600
I agree with him.

965
01:10:22,720 --> 01:10:25,440
I say what goes around comes around.

966
01:10:30,280 --> 01:10:31,640
- Are you OK?
- Yes.

967
01:10:31,720 --> 01:10:34,560
- I was worried. It's late.
- I had some business.

968
01:10:34,640 --> 01:10:37,080
- Mrs Ames is waiting.
- Any messages?

969
01:10:37,160 --> 01:10:40,000
Yeah. An odd one.
A Detective O'Donnell called.

970
01:10:40,080 --> 01:10:42,200
He wanted to talk to you about something.

971
01:10:42,280 --> 01:10:46,840
I tried to get him to tell me what,
but he said he only wants to talk with you.

972
01:10:49,880 --> 01:10:51,520
# He says "Murder", he says

973
01:10:51,600 --> 01:10:54,040
# Every time we kiss,
he says "Murder", he says

974
01:10:54,120 --> 01:10:56,720
# Keep it up like this
and then "Murder", he says

975
01:10:56,800 --> 01:10:59,080
# In that impossible tone

976
01:10:59,320 --> 01:11:04,320
# Will bring on
nobody's murder but his own

977
01:11:05,560 --> 01:11:08,080
That was not such a great movie,
but it was fun.

978
01:11:08,160 --> 01:11:11,600
Yeah, I liked it. I think maybe
when I'm older, I wanna be an actress.

979
01:11:11,680 --> 01:11:16,040
Don't be an actress. I want you to be
on the Supreme Court, or a doctor.

980
01:11:16,160 --> 01:11:18,680
You know, show business is dog-eat-dog.

981
01:11:18,760 --> 01:11:23,520
It's worse than dog-eat-dog. It's dog
doesn't return other dog's phone calls.

982
01:11:23,640 --> 01:11:25,920
Which reminds me,
I should check my service.

983
01:11:26,040 --> 01:11:28,600
Though I haven't had a message
in seven years.

984
01:11:28,680 --> 01:11:30,880
I call up and I hear the girls giggling.

985
01:11:30,960 --> 01:11:33,000
- How's Halley?
- She's great.

986
01:11:33,120 --> 01:11:35,080
I'm gonna make my move there, I think.

987
01:11:35,200 --> 01:11:39,440
But I have this ethical dilemma cos I'm
married. You shouldn't know about that.

988
01:11:39,520 --> 01:11:42,400
Clifford Stern. Any messages?
Can you check, please?

989
01:11:42,480 --> 01:11:44,760
My heart says one thing.
My head says another.

990
01:11:44,880 --> 01:11:48,800
Very hard to get your heart and head
together in life. Let me teach you that.

991
01:11:48,880 --> 01:11:50,520
Mine aren't even friendly.

992
01:11:50,640 --> 01:11:52,600
Yes.

993
01:11:55,680 --> 01:11:57,640
Really?

994
01:12:02,280 --> 01:12:04,240
No.

995
01:12:06,280 --> 01:12:08,240
OK, thank you.

996
01:12:11,160 --> 01:12:13,120
What's wrong?

997
01:12:15,520 --> 01:12:17,480
Professor Levy

998
01:12:17,600 --> 01:12:19,960
committed suicide.

999
01:12:21,000 --> 01:12:23,520
But we must always remember

1000
01:12:23,600 --> 01:12:26,560
that we, when we are born,

1001
01:12:27,240 --> 01:12:33,400
we need a great deal of love
in order to persuade us to stay in life.

1002
01:12:33,520 --> 01:12:35,640
Once we get that love

1003
01:12:35,720 --> 01:12:37,280
it usually lasts us.

1004
01:12:37,360 --> 01:12:39,920
But the universe is a pretty cold place.

1005
01:12:40,000 --> 01:12:43,040
It's we who invest it with our feelings.

1006
01:12:43,680 --> 01:12:46,360
And, under certain conditions,

1007
01:12:46,440 --> 01:12:49,960
we feel that the thing
isn't worth it any more.

1008
01:12:50,040 --> 01:12:54,240
I came as soon as I heard.
I thought you might not wanna be alone.

1009
01:12:54,320 --> 01:12:56,440
God, it's been terrible. You know?

1010
01:12:56,560 --> 01:12:59,160
I called... The guy was not sick at all.

1011
01:12:59,240 --> 01:13:02,600
And he left a note, a simple note:
"I've gone out the window."

1012
01:13:02,680 --> 01:13:07,040
This is a major intellectual, and this is
his note. What the hell does that mean?

1013
01:13:07,160 --> 01:13:10,360
This guy was a role model.
You'd think he'd leave a decent note.

1014
01:13:10,480 --> 01:13:13,000
Did he have family or anything?

1015
01:13:13,080 --> 01:13:16,280
No. They were all killed in the war.
That's what's so strange.

1016
01:13:16,400 --> 01:13:19,360
He's seen the worst side of life.
He always was affirmative.

1017
01:13:19,480 --> 01:13:22,680
Always said yes to life. Yes, yes.
Now today, he said no.

1018
01:13:22,800 --> 01:13:26,160
Can you imagine his students?
How shattered they're gonna be?

1019
01:13:26,280 --> 01:13:29,120
I don't know from suicide.
Where I grew up in Brooklyn,

1020
01:13:29,200 --> 01:13:31,960
nobody committed suicide.
Everyone was too unhappy.

1021
01:13:32,040 --> 01:13:34,400
Boy, this will put a damper on the show.

1022
01:13:34,520 --> 01:13:38,720
I got 600,000 feet of film on this guy
and he's telling how great life is,

1023
01:13:38,840 --> 01:13:40,800
and now what am I gonna do?

1024
01:13:40,920 --> 01:13:43,280
I'll cut it up and make it into guitar picks.

1025
01:13:43,360 --> 01:13:48,880
I was thinking. No matter how elaborate
a philosophical system you work out,

1026
01:13:49,000 --> 01:13:51,880
in the end, it's gotta be incomplete.

1027
01:13:52,600 --> 01:13:56,200
I've been so annoyed all day.
I'm sorry for seeming cranky.

1028
01:13:56,320 --> 01:13:58,280
- I understand.
- This was such a blow.

1029
01:13:58,400 --> 01:14:01,080
I just thought
you might want some company.

1030
01:14:03,880 --> 01:14:06,000
No, don't do that.

1031
01:14:06,120 --> 01:14:09,320
It's something that
I've wanted to do now for weeks.

1032
01:14:09,440 --> 01:14:11,560
- You must know that.
- You're married.

1033
01:14:11,680 --> 01:14:15,280
Yes, I'm married,
but that's not gonna... last.

1034
01:14:15,400 --> 01:14:19,160
- I mean, you know...
- Well, you know, I'm... I'm not ready.

1035
01:14:21,800 --> 01:14:24,160
Is there something you're not telling me?

1036
01:14:24,280 --> 01:14:26,400
- No.
- Is there anybody else?

1037
01:14:26,520 --> 01:14:30,280
- I just don't want you to say it's Lester.
- It's me. It's just me.

1038
01:14:30,400 --> 01:14:35,000
I... I guess I haven't
gotten over my divorce yet.

1039
01:14:35,120 --> 01:14:38,560
And also, I feel unsettled about my career.

1040
01:14:38,640 --> 01:14:41,000
You don't know this
but I'm very ambitious,

1041
01:14:41,120 --> 01:14:44,400
and that's an area
that I'd like to get consolidated.

1042
01:14:44,520 --> 01:14:47,120
I just feel, you know, unsettled.

1043
01:15:01,000 --> 01:15:03,960
- Don't confuse me.
- I'm not trying to confuse you.

1044
01:15:04,080 --> 01:15:06,040
I don't know what I'm doing.

1045
01:15:07,040 --> 01:15:10,080
I better go. I should just leave.

1046
01:15:10,160 --> 01:15:13,280
- You just got here.
- I know, but I... you know.

1047
01:15:13,360 --> 01:15:17,640
- I'm sorry. I didn't mean to...
- No, that's OK. It's not... I'll see you soon.

1048
01:15:17,760 --> 01:15:19,960
I'll just... I'll be seeing you.

1049
01:15:23,640 --> 01:15:25,640
Please come in.

1050
01:15:26,680 --> 01:15:30,080
We read about it in the paper.
It's a terrible thing.

1051
01:15:31,000 --> 01:15:33,080
She'd been coming here for years.

1052
01:15:33,160 --> 01:15:35,160
- Please sit down.
- Thank you.

1053
01:15:35,720 --> 01:15:37,720
Just a couple of questions, Doctor.

1054
01:15:37,800 --> 01:15:43,000
The record shows that she phoned you
here and at your home a number of times.

1055
01:15:43,080 --> 01:15:44,960
She was worried about her eyes.

1056
01:15:45,040 --> 01:15:48,760
- What was she suffering from?
- Nothing serious. She...

1057
01:15:49,520 --> 01:15:51,960
She had light flashes
and they alarmed her.

1058
01:15:52,040 --> 01:15:54,520
I could never find
anything very wrong with her.

1059
01:15:54,600 --> 01:15:57,360
And I told her that
it's just a common occurrence.

1060
01:15:57,440 --> 01:16:00,560
- She was a hypochondriac?
- No, I wouldn't say that but

1061
01:16:00,640 --> 01:16:02,640
she was concerned.

1062
01:16:03,600 --> 01:16:07,160
And there's nothing she ever said
that might be relevant to the case?

1063
01:16:07,240 --> 01:16:09,240
Personal life? Friends?

1064
01:16:09,320 --> 01:16:11,320
No. Not really.

1065
01:16:12,120 --> 01:16:14,120
How did she come to you?

1066
01:16:15,400 --> 01:16:17,600
You know, I honestly can't remember.

1067
01:16:17,680 --> 01:16:20,600
- Possibly another patient.
- Can I get that name?

1068
01:16:20,680 --> 01:16:23,960
Well, it was a while ago
and I... I treat so many patients.

1069
01:16:24,040 --> 01:16:26,240
Might it be in your records?

1070
01:16:26,320 --> 01:16:29,320
No. No, I... I doubt it very much.

1071
01:16:30,840 --> 01:16:33,760
- Well, I'm sorry to take up your time.
- That's all right.

1072
01:16:33,840 --> 01:16:37,160
If you remember anything,
will you give me a call?

1073
01:16:37,240 --> 01:16:38,520
Sure.

1074
01:16:38,600 --> 01:16:40,600
- Thank you.
- Pleasure.

1075
01:16:49,960 --> 01:16:52,160
Judah, you're having a breakdown.

1076
01:16:52,240 --> 01:16:55,400
The police know she phoned me.
I lied, but they saw through it.

1077
01:16:55,480 --> 01:16:59,000
- I can't take this, Jack.
- Pull yourself together or you'll blow it.

1078
01:16:59,080 --> 01:17:02,200
I did it, and it's irrevocable,
and now I'm gonna pay.

1079
01:17:02,280 --> 01:17:05,960
I had to fight an urge to confess
to the police. I want this off my mind.

1080
01:17:06,040 --> 01:17:10,600
Listen. I'm in this with you. I helped you
out and I don't wanna go to jail for it.

1081
01:17:10,680 --> 01:17:16,920
You may not care if you drag me down
with you, but I'm not letting that happen.

1082
01:17:17,000 --> 01:17:20,800
- What the hell is that? A threat?
- Just be a man. You're in the clear.

1083
01:17:20,880 --> 01:17:23,200
- You'll rub me out, too?
- Don't talk nonsense.

1084
01:17:23,280 --> 01:17:25,840
What did you mean by saying
you won't let it happen?

1085
01:17:25,920 --> 01:17:28,640
You're my brother.
You've helped me out financially.

1086
01:17:28,720 --> 01:17:30,800
I did you a favour when you needed it.

1087
01:17:30,880 --> 01:17:32,880
Now all of a sudden you want to confess?

1088
01:17:32,960 --> 01:17:36,440
The time to confess was to Miriam,
about your mistress. Not about this.

1089
01:17:36,520 --> 01:17:41,240
This is murder. You paid for it,
I engineered it. It's over. Forget about it.

1090
01:17:42,280 --> 01:17:44,280
One sin leads to a deeper sin.

1091
01:17:44,360 --> 01:17:49,120
- Now you sound like Papa.
- Adultery, fornication, lies, killing.

1092
01:17:49,200 --> 01:17:52,440
- Shut up already.
- Or you'll have your friends shut me up?

1093
01:17:52,520 --> 01:17:55,360
One phone call,
like pushing a button, right?

1094
01:18:30,600 --> 01:18:35,000
Judah, I don't know what's wrong with
you these days. You're a different person.

1095
01:18:35,080 --> 01:18:37,080
I believe in God, Miriam.

1096
01:18:38,040 --> 01:18:42,720
I know it... because without God
the world is a cesspool.

1097
01:18:42,800 --> 01:18:47,560
You're drinking steadily and every day.
You never used to. It's something new.

1098
01:18:47,640 --> 01:18:50,040
- God, it's hot in here.
- Well, maybe we should go.

1099
01:18:50,120 --> 01:18:54,320
- Don't tell me what I should do, dammit!
- Judah, will you calm down!

1100
01:18:56,760 --> 01:18:59,520
I don't feel well. I'm gonna get a little air.

1101
01:18:59,600 --> 01:19:01,600
No, you stay here.

1102
01:19:23,840 --> 01:19:26,320
Look, this story on the homeless,
it's too long.

1103
01:19:26,400 --> 01:19:29,760
I want five pages. Make sure
he gets five real pages out of it.

1104
01:19:29,840 --> 01:19:33,360
He tells the secretary to type it tighter.
He doesn't take anything out.

1105
01:19:33,440 --> 01:19:35,240
I want Joe Hanson off the show.

1106
01:19:35,320 --> 01:19:40,720
He doesn't write funny. If he has cancer,
I'll send him flowers. I want him off.

1107
01:19:40,800 --> 01:19:44,320
Jesus! Doesn't anybody
know how to write funny any more?

1108
01:19:44,400 --> 01:19:48,360
Am I supposed to write it myself?
Direct it myself? Produce it myself?

1109
01:19:48,440 --> 01:19:52,800
I can't believe this! Look at those people
out there! Look out the window at them.

1110
01:19:52,880 --> 01:19:56,120
These people are lookin'
for something funny in their lives!

1111
01:19:56,200 --> 01:20:00,360
You're givin' 'em straight lines!
They're waitin' for something funny!

1112
01:20:18,120 --> 01:20:20,120
This is terrible.

1113
01:20:20,200 --> 01:20:22,200
What are you doing to me?

1114
01:20:22,280 --> 01:20:25,000
This is supposed to be
the profile of a creative mind.

1115
01:20:25,360 --> 01:20:30,200
It's tough for a woman in this profession.
I can make it easier for you.

1116
01:20:30,280 --> 01:20:33,240
What is this? When did you shoot that?

1117
01:20:33,320 --> 01:20:36,520
I was lurking around the corner.
I couldn't resist.

1118
01:20:36,600 --> 01:20:41,680
I don't wanna do it in kind of a vulgar way
and just take it off what I see here.

1119
01:20:41,760 --> 01:20:44,920
I wanna find out what's in here,
so I gotta spend some time with you.

1120
01:20:45,000 --> 01:20:48,520
We'll have a little dinner together, just...

1121
01:20:48,600 --> 01:20:51,000
OK, step aside. I'm taking over this film.

1122
01:20:51,080 --> 01:20:54,560
- What? You can't finish my film.
- I can't? Read your contract.

1123
01:20:54,640 --> 01:20:58,000
- You promised.
- Look, the idea was to show the real me.

1124
01:20:58,080 --> 01:21:02,920
I may not be perfect, but I don't promote
values that... Let me quote you exactly:

1125
01:21:03,000 --> 01:21:06,040
"That deaden the sensibilities
of a great democracy".

1126
01:21:06,120 --> 01:21:08,840
You're fired, Cliff!
You're out! Get outta here!

1127
01:21:08,920 --> 01:21:11,280
Go! Thank you! Goodbye!

1128
01:21:11,360 --> 01:21:15,560
If it bends, it's funny. If it breaks, it isn't.

1129
01:21:16,400 --> 01:21:20,160
Come on now. Don't get discouraged.
You have your own personal vision.

1130
01:21:20,240 --> 01:21:24,280
Why is he so upset? You'd think nobody
was ever compared to Mussolini before.

1131
01:21:24,360 --> 01:21:29,400
I had no idea you would cut the film like
this. I'd have told you they'd never use it.

1132
01:21:29,480 --> 01:21:31,880
They want an upbeat profile of Lester.

1133
01:21:31,960 --> 01:21:35,560
Now he's gonna re-cut it
and make himself into a saint.

1134
